# Face Recognition Project — Complete Explanation

## What This Project Does

This project uses your **webcam** to detect human faces in real-time, recognize **who** the face belongs to, and display the person's name on screen. It also includes fun extras like applying Instagram-style filters, overlaying glasses & mustache on detected faces, recording video, and creating timelapses.

---

## How Face Recognition Works (The Big Picture)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A["📸 Training Images\n(images/ folder)"] --> B["🧠 faces-train.py\nTrain the model"]
    B --> C["💾 face-trainner.yml\n(Saved model)"]
    B --> D["🏷️ face-labels.pickle\n(Name↔ID map)"]
    C --> E["🎥 faces.py\nLive recognition"]
    D --> E
    E --> F["👤 'Hello, JK!'\nRecognized face on screen"]
```

### Two-Phase Process

| Phase | Script | What Happens |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| **Phase 1: Training** | [faces-train.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/faces-train.py) | Scans your training photos, finds faces in them, learns what each person looks like, saves the trained model |
| **Phase 2: Recognition** | [faces.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/faces.py) | Opens webcam, detects faces in each frame, compares them against the trained model, shows the person's name |

