#### [Face_detect.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/Face_detect.py) — Alternative Approach

**Purpose:** A different face recognition approach using the `face_recognition` library (built on dlib's deep learning model) instead of OpenCV's LBPH.

**How it differs from [faces.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/faces.py):**
- Uses **deep learning embeddings** (128-dimensional vectors) instead of LBPH histograms
- Generally more accurate but requires the `face_recognition` + `dlib` packages
- Compares face "encodings" using `face_recognition.compare_faces()`

> **⚠️ Issue:** This script has a bug — `SimpleFacerec()` is called on line 16 before it's imported on line 20. The referenced images (`Messi1.webp`) are also not in the repo.

---

### 🎨 Video Effects Scripts

#### [filter.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/filter.py) — Live Camera Filters

**Purpose:** Applies Instagram-style filters to your live webcam feed.

**6 filters available:**

| Filter | Function | What It Does |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| Hue/Saturation | [apply_hue_saturation()](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/filter.py#25-37) | Fills saturation & value channels to create a vivid color effect |
| Sepia | [apply_sepia()](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/filter.py#48-55) | Overlays warm brown tones (old-photo look) |
| Color Overlay | [apply_color_overlay()](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/filter.py#39-46) | Tints the frame with a custom RGB color |
| Invert | [apply_invert()](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/filter.py#91-93) | Flips all pixel values (negative effect) |
| Circle Blur | [apply_circle_focus_blur()](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/filter.py#63-77) | Keeps center sharp, blurs edges (tilt-shift look) |
| Portrait | [portrait_mode()](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/filter.py#79-89) | Attempts background blur using brightness thresholds |

Each filter uses `cv2.addWeighted()` for alpha blending — mixing the effect layer with the original frame.

---

#### [glasses_and_stash.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/glasses_and_stash.py) — AR Face Overlay

**Purpose:** Detects your eyes and nose in real-time, then overlays glasses and a mustache PNG image on top.

**How it works:**
1. Detects **face** using [haarcascade_frontalface_default.xml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/cascades/data/haarcascade_frontalface_default.xml)
2. Within the face region, detects **eyes** using [frontalEyes35x16.xml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/cascades/third-party/frontalEyes35x16.xml)
3. Within the face region, detects **nose** using [Nose18x15.xml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/cascades/third-party/Nose18x15.xml)
4. Resizes the glasses/mustache PNG to match the detected region size
5. Alpha-blends each pixel (respects PNG transparency)

```python
# Pixel-by-pixel overlay (preserving transparency)
for i in range(0, gw):
    for j in range(0, gh):
        if glasses2[i, j][3] != 0:  # If pixel is not transparent
            roi_color[ey + i, ex + j] = glasses2[i, j]  # Place it
```

---

#### [watermark.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/watermark.py) — Video Watermarking

**Purpose:** Adds a semi-transparent logo (coffee cup image) to the bottom-right corner of your live video feed.

Creates a full-frame transparent overlay, places the watermark pixels into it, then blends with `cv2.addWeighted()` at 25% opacity.

---

#### [timelapse.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/timelapse.py) — Timelapse Creator

**Purpose:** Captures one frame every 0.25 seconds for 20 seconds, saves them as individual JPGs, then stitches them together into a video.

**Two phases:**
1. **Capture:** Saves numbered [.jpg](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/1.jpg) frames to `images/timelapse/`
2. **Stitch:** [images_to_video()](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/timelapse.py#41-53) reads all JPGs sorted by time, writes them into a `.mp4`, then deletes the individual frames

---

#### [record.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/record.py) — Video Recorder

**Purpose:** Records your webcam feed to an AVI file at 720p, 24fps. Minimal script — just captures and writes frames in a loop.

---

### 🔨 Utility Scripts

#### [utils.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/utils.py) — Shared Utilities

**Purpose:** Provides two reusable utilities used by multiple scripts:

**[image_resize(image, width=None, height=None)](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/utils.py#5-31)**
- Resizes an image while maintaining aspect ratio
- Specify either width OR height, the other dimension is calculated automatically

**[CFEVideoConf](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/utils.py#34-81) class**
- Manages video output configuration: resolution presets (360p–4K), codec selection (XVID)
- Used by [filter.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/filter.py), [glasses_and_stash.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/glasses_and_stash.py), [watermark.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/watermark.py), [timelapse.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/timelapse.py), [record.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/record.py)

---

#### [base.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/base.py) — Minimal Camera Loop

**Purpose:** The simplest possible webcam script — opens the camera, shows the feed, press 'q' to quit. Starting template for all other scripts.

#### [camera-test.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/camera-test.py) — Camera Test

**Purpose:** Verifies your webcam is working by showing two windows: one color, one grayscale.

#### [res-change.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/res-change.py) — Resolution Demo

**Purpose:** Demonstrates resolution scaling — shows the webcam at 30% and 500% scale to understand `cv2.resize()`. Also has preset functions ([make_1080p()](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/res-change.py#6-9), [make_720p()](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/res-change.py#10-13), [make_480p()](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/res-change.py#14-17)).

