### 📁 Asset Directories

#### `cascades/data/` — Haar Cascade Models

Pre-trained XML classifiers from OpenCV for detecting specific features:

| File | Detects |
|------|---------|
| [haarcascade_frontalface_alt2.xml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/cascades/data/haarcascade_frontalface_alt2.xml) | Faces (front-facing) — **main one used** |
| [haarcascade_frontalface_default.xml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/cascades/data/haarcascade_frontalface_default.xml) | Faces (front-facing) — used by AR overlay |
| [haarcascade_eye.xml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/cascades/data/haarcascade_eye.xml) | Eyes |
| [haarcascade_smile.xml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/cascades/data/haarcascade_smile.xml) | Smiles |
| [haarcascade_profileface.xml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/cascades/data/haarcascade_profileface.xml) | Side-view faces |
| [haarcascade_fullbody.xml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/cascades/data/haarcascade_fullbody.xml) | Full bodies |
| [haarcascade_upperbody.xml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/cascades/data/haarcascade_upperbody.xml) | Upper bodies |
| [haarcascade_frontalcatface.xml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/cascades/data/haarcascade_frontalcatface.xml) | Cat faces 🐱 |
| Others... | License plates, left/right eyes, etc. |

#### `cascades/third-party/`

| File | Used By |
|------|---------|
| [frontalEyes35x16.xml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/cascades/third-party/frontalEyes35x16.xml) | [glasses_and_stash.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/glasses_and_stash.py) — detects eye region for glasses overlay |
| [Nose18x15.xml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/cascades/third-party/Nose18x15.xml) | [glasses_and_stash.py](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/glasses_and_stash.py) — detects nose region for mustache overlay |

#### [images/](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/timelapse.py#41-53) — Training Data

Each sub-folder = one person. The folder name becomes the label:
- `images/Jk/` → label "jk" (your photos)
- `images/emilia-clarke/` → label "emilia-clarke"
- `images/kit-harington/` → label "kit-harington"
- `images/peter-dinklage/` → label "peter-dinklage"
- `images/fun/` → AR overlay assets (glasses.png, mustache.png)
- `images/logo/` → watermark image (cfe-coffee.png)

#### [recognizers/face-trainner.yml](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/recognizers/face-trainner.yml)
The **trained LBPH model** (6.9 MB). Contains the learned face patterns from training. This file is what makes recognition possible without retraining every time.

#### [pickles/face-labels.pickle](file:///e:/projects/Face_recognisation/src/pickles/face-labels.pickle)
A serialized Python dictionary mapping person names to numeric IDs:
```python
{"jk": 0, "emilia-clarke": 1, "kit-harington": 2, ...}
```
The recognizer outputs numeric IDs; this file translates them back to names.

#### `lessons/`
Tutorial versions of some scripts — more heavily commented for learning purposes. These are older versions that were moved here to keep the main `src/` directory clean.

---

## How Everything Connects

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph Training["Phase 1: Training"]
        IMG["images/<br/>Jk/, emilia-clarke/, etc."] --> FT["faces-train.py"]
        HC1["cascades/data/<br/>haarcascade_frontalface_alt2.xml"] --> FT
        FT --> MODEL["recognizers/<br/>face-trainner.yml"]
        FT --> LABELS["pickles/<br/>face-labels.pickle"]
    end
    
    subgraph Recognition["Phase 2: Recognition"]
        MODEL --> FACES["faces.py"]
        LABELS --> FACES
        HC1 --> FACES
        CAM["Webcam"] --> FACES
        FACES --> OUTPUT["Display: Name + Box"]
    end
    
    subgraph Effects["Extras"]
        CAM --> FILTER["filter.py<br/>6 live filters"]
        CAM --> AR["glasses_and_stash.py<br/>AR overlays"]
        CAM --> WM["watermark.py<br/>Logo overlay"]
        CAM --> TL["timelapse.py<br/>Timelapse creator"]
        CAM --> REC["record.py<br/>Video recorder"]
    end
    
    UTILS["utils.py<br/>CFEVideoConf + image_resize"] -.-> FILTER
    UTILS -.-> AR
    UTILS -.-> WM
    UTILS -.-> TL
    UTILS -.-> REC
```
